718891f-a.title: Manhattan: Church Street - White Street
718891f-a.text:
Church Street, west side, south fom and including White Street, showing the Eighth Ave., Subway in process of construction. In the
right background is the Woolwoth Building.
September 9, 1928.
P. L Sperr.
718891f-a.folder: Church Street & White Street, Manhattan, NY

718890f-a.title: Manhattan: Church Street - White Street
718890f-a.text:
At the convergance of Church Street and the new Sixth Ave. Extension at white Street. Shown on the right, is the west side of Church Street, north to and including Canal Street. Prominently shown, is the N.Y. Telephone Euilding which fronts on Walker, Lispenard and Church Streets and the new
Sixth Ave. Extension.
June 3, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
718890f-a.folder: Church Street & White Street, Manhattan, NY

718892f-a.title: Manhattan: Church Street - White Street
718892f-a.text:
Church Street, east side, south from but not including White to and including Franklin Streets, as seen from the Sixth Ave., extension
at Walker Street.
March 19, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
718892f-a.folder: Church Street & White Street, Manhattan, NY

718893f-a.title: Manhattan: Church Street - White Street
718893f-a.text:
(1)
Church Street, east side, north from White to Walker Streets as viewed eastward from and across Sixth Ave. Extension. The white 3-story structure at the N.E. corner of White Street bears No. 34 on same. The large office building in the background is No. 401 Broadway,
at the N.W. corner of Walker Street.
May 2, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
Church Street,West side,looking North from White Street.
July 12th,1939.
